    "explanation": "Imperforate hymen: The young girls <br>present with colicky abdominal pain which is often cyclic. Menarche has not yet <br>set in; however, secondary sexual characters have been well developed. As the <br>vagina gets progressively and increasingly distended with menstrual blood <br>(hematocolpos), pressure symptoms follow (difficulty during micturition finally <br>ends up with urinary retention). If the condition is neglected, vaginal distension <br>progressed beyond the hematocolpos to hematosalpinx and hematometra. <br>Reference: Shaw, 15th Ed., Pg. 96.",
