    "answer": "d",
    "explanation": "DEC is the specific drug for Lymphatic Filariasis (Wuchereria bancrofti), it is  <br> entirely useless against dog tapeworm cysts. <br> 73. Which one of the following deadly infections is NOT amenable to Post- <br> Exposure Prophylaxis (PEP) using specific ready-made Immunoglobulin? <br> (a) Rabies <br> (b) Tetanus <br> (c) Hepatitis B <br> (d) HIV <br> Answer: (d) <br>  <br> Tip: We have hyperimmune serums to instantly neutralize Rabies, Tetanus, and  <br> Hep B viruses in the blood. We do NOT possess a neutralizing antibody serum  <br> for HIV (we must use antiretroviral chemicals instead).",
