    "explanation": "(a) Lymph Nodes <br> (b) Genitourinary Tract <br> (c) Skeletal System (Spine) <br> (d) Spleen <br> Answer: (d) <br> Tip: TB famously attacks the neck nodes (Scrofula), the kidneys, and the spine  <br> (Pott's Disease). Isolated splenic TB is extraordinarily rare.",
