    "explanation": "(a) Drastically reduced skin folds <br> (b) Severely reduced mid-arm circumference <br> (c) Loss of subcutaneous fat <br> (d) Predominant severe protein wasting and massive pitting edema <br> Answer: (d) <br> Tip: Marasmus means the child is starving of EVERYTHING (Calories + Protein),  <br> looking like skin and bones. Kwashiorkor is exclusively a PROTEIN deficiency,  <br> leading to massive fluid leaking out of blood vessels causing severe whole-body  <br> edema.",
