    "question": "A 35-year-old male presents with polyuria (urine output > 4 Liters/day)  and noticeably LOW urine osmolality (< 250 mOsm/L). Which of the following  conditions could be the cause? 1. Psychogenic Polydipsia. 2. Solute Diuresis. 3. Central Diabetes Insipidus. 4. Nephrogenic Diabetes Insipidus. Select the correct statements:",
