    "question": "The \"Carey Coombs Murmur\" is clinically characterized by:",
    "options": {
      "a": "A harsh pansystolic murmur",
      "b": "A soft, mid-diastolic murmur best heard with the bell of a stethoscope  during acute Rheumatic Fever (Mitral Valvulitis)",
      "c": "An early diastolic murmur of aortic regurgitation",
      "d": "A late systolic click"
    },
