    "num": "31",
    "question": "Regarding the step-wise management of Idiopathic Thrombocytopenic  Purpura (ITP), which statements are CORRECT? 1. Patients with active spontaneous bleeding or platelets strictly < 30 x 10⁹/L require immediate high-dose Glucocorticoids. 2. IV Immunoglobulins (IVIG) are given to rapidly raise platelet counts in active bleeding. 3. Life-threatening bleeding demands emergency Platelet Transfusions. Select the correct answer:",
