    "question": "A massive, macrosomic infant born to an uncontrolled Diabetic Mother  faces an incredibly high risk of suffering from which severe neonatal metabolic  complications within the first 28 days of life? 1. Profound Hypoglycemia. 2. Severe Hypercalcemia. 3. Hyperbilirubinemia (Jaundice). 4. Hypomagnesemia leading to Tetany. Select the correct answer:",
