    "question": "A 38-week primigravida is receiving an aggressive IV Oxytocin drip to  blindly augment her sluggish labor. A newly appointed resident accidentally runs  the drip rate incredibly high (>30 mIU/minute). The mother suddenly develops  profound confusion and violent convulsions. What specific, deadly electrolyte  imbalance has the drug caused?",
